1) Check Current Version
gitlab-rake gitlab:env:info
gitlab-rake gitlab:check
gitlab-psql --version
gitlab-rake gitlab:env:info | grep "DB Version"
2) Take Backup
gitlab-backup create

Backup configuration files:
cp -rp /etc/gitlab /root/gitlab_backup/
cp -rp /var/opt/gitlab /root/gitlab_var_backup/

3) rpm -Uvh gitlab-ee-13.0.14-ee.0.el8.x86_64.rpm  (or ) yum localinstall gitlab-ee-13.0.14-ee.0.el8.x86_64.rpm

After installation:
gitlab-ctl reconfigure
gitlab-ctl restart
verify
gitlab-rake gitlab:env:info

No PostgreSQL upgrade is required just to move from 12.10 to 13.0.
6. Run Database Migrations Status
gitlab-rake db:migrate:status
7. Health Check
gitlab-rake gitlab:check SANITIZE=true
gitlab-ctl status
8. Upgrade to Latest 13.x
After successfully running on 13.0.x:
yum install gitlab-ee-13.12.15-ee.0.el8
gitlab-ctl reconfigure
gitlab-ctl restart



